* missing 6502 instructions:
  when done, remove "unimplemented instruction" code and messages
* floppy disk support:
  - disk writing
  - read-only disks
  - other disk formats than .nib
* function keys:
  - to emulate ESC and Ctrl-C keys
  - to hot-load a floppy into a drive
  - to exit the program
* command-line options:
  - to intercept NMI
  - to disable disks
  - etc
* screen modes:
  - low resolution
  - mixed low resolution/text
  - high resolution
* more hardware emulation:
  - sound
  - game paddles
